```python
class ObjectIdStr(str):
    @classmethod
    def __get_validators__(cls):
        yield cls.validate

    @classmethod
    def validate(cls, v):
        try:
            ObjectId(str(v))
        except InvalidId:
            raise ValuerError("Not a valid ObjectId")
        return str(v)
```

this way I can either pass a valid ObjectId string or an ObjectId instance.

